text: L. australis may refer to: * Lagenorhynchus australis, the Peale's dolphin, a small dolphin species found in the waters around Tierra del Fuego at the foot of South America * Livistona australis, the cabbage-tree palm, a plant species * Limnohabitans australis, a planktonic freshwater bacterium affiliated with the class Betaproteobacteria and the family Comamonadaceae ==See also== * Australis (disambiguation)
title: L. australis
